## Phase 2: Wire up `webhook-meta` (The Traffic Director)

**Goal**: Make `webhook-meta` check the flag and route to Code Engine OR n8n.

### Changes

#### [MODIFY] [webhook-meta/index.ts](file:///c:/QuickRevert/app.quickrevert.tech/supabase/functions/webhook-meta/index.ts)

Currently, after all the identity resolution, contact upsert, and activity logging, the function calls:
```typescript
await triggerWorkflows(payloadData, activeRoutes.routes, activeRoutes.workflows);
```

We add a check **right before** this line (in both the messaging branch ~line 442 and the changes branch ~line 579):

```typescript
// Check if this user has Code Engine enabled
const useCodeEngine = await checkCodeEngineFlag(supabaseClient, accountsData[0].user_id);

if (useCodeEngine) {
    // Route to Code Engine
    await supabaseClient.functions.invoke('execute-automation', {
        body: {
            userId: accountsData[0].user_id,
            instagramAccountId: internalAccountId,
            triggerType: /* 'post_comment' | 'user_dm' | 'story_reply' */,
            eventData: {
                commentId: /* ... */,
                commentText: /* ... */,
                messageText: /* ... */,
                postbackPayload: /* ... */,
                postId: mediaId,
                from: { id: targetUserId, username: resolvedUsername }
            }
        }
    });
} else {
    // Legacy n8n routing (unchanged)
    await triggerWorkflows(payloadData, activeRoutes.routes, activeRoutes.workflows);
}
```

We also add a helper that piggybacks on the existing `checkUserDmLimit` query (so we don't add an extra DB call):

```typescript
async function checkCodeEngineFlag(supabaseClient: any, userId: string): Promise<boolean> {
    const { data } = await supabaseClient
        .from('user_limits')
        .select('use_code_engine')
        .eq('user_id', userId)
        .maybeSingle();
    return data?.use_code_engine === true;
}
```

> [!TIP]
> Even better: we already call `checkUserDmLimit()` which queries `user_limits`. We can add `use_code_engine` to that same SELECT and return it alongside the DM limit check — **zero additional DB calls**.

### What does NOT change
- All identity resolution, contact upsert, activity logging — stays exactly the same
- The `resolveRoutes()` function — still runs (we need the `matchedAutomationId` for logging)
- n8n users — their `use_code_engine` is `false`, so `triggerWorkflows()` runs as before

### Testing
1. Deploy updated `webhook-meta`
