## Phase 3: Build the Executor Functions & Follow-up Scheduler

**Goal**: Implement the actual execution logic split by trigger type, along with advanced features (Carousel support, recursive Menu Flows, and Scheduled Follow-up DMs).

### 3A. Master Router

#### [MODIFY] [execute-automation/index.ts](file:///c:/QuickRevert/app.quickrevert.tech/supabase/functions/execute-automation/index.ts)

Refactor into a lightweight router that:
1. Receives the event from `webhook-meta`
2. Fetches the Instagram account + access token
3. Matches the automation(s) using trigger config
4. Delegates to the correct executor function

```typescript
// Pseudocode
const matched = matchAutomations(automations, triggerType, eventData);

for (const automation of matched) {
    switch (triggerType) {
        case 'post_comment':
            await supabase.functions.invoke('execute-post-comment', {
                body: { automation, eventData, accessToken }
            });
            break;
        case 'user_dm':
        case 'user_directed_messages':
            await supabase.functions.invoke('execute-dm', {
                body: { automation, eventData, accessToken, contactId }
            });
            break;
        case 'story_reply':
            await supabase.functions.invoke('execute-story', {
                body: { automation, eventData, accessToken }
            });
            break;
    }
}
```

The trigger matching logic already exists in the current `execute-automation`. We keep it here in the router.

