### 3B. Post Comment Executor

#### [NEW] `execute-post-comment/index.ts`

Handles the `post_comment` trigger. Responsibilities:
- Reply to the comment with round-robin templates via `/{comment_id}/replies`
- Send DM to commenter via `/me/messages` (text, buttons, or carousel)
- **Carousel Support**: When action has `dmType === 'carousel'` and `carouselCards` is present, format them as a `generic` template element list for Facebook's Send API:
  ```typescript
  const elements = action.carouselCards.map((card: any) => ({
      title: card.title.substring(0, 80),
      subtitle: card.subtitle.substring(0, 80),
      image_url: card.imageUrl,
      buttons: card.buttons.slice(0, 3).map((b: any) => ({
          type: b.url ? "web_url" : "postback",
          title: b.text.substring(0, 20),
          url: b.url,
          payload: b.url ? undefined : `${b.text}_${automationId}`
      }))
  }));
  ```
- Follow-to-unlock guard (check `is_user_follow_business`)
- **Init Follow-up DM**: If the automation has a scheduled follow-up active, insert a record in the `scheduled_followups` table (see 3E).
- Log execution to `automation_activities`

